MOTOROLA'S PROFIT DECLINE

Motorola's fourth quarter earnings suffered a 16-per-cent decline to
$432 million over the same period last year, despite a 13-per-cent rise
in revenues to $7.3 billion.  A decline in US orders and pricing
pressure in overseas markets were blamed for the disappointing
performance which followed last month's profits' warning by rival
Nokia.





