Swedish telecommunications manufacturer Ericsson has won two contracts
to expand existing cellular networks.  The first, worth SKr1 billion
(#97 million), is to expand the GSM network of Telia Mobitel, the
Swedish cellular operator.  The other is with Japanese regional
operator Tokyo Digital Phone and is valued at SKr450 million (#44
million).  The service was launched in April 1994 (Mobile
Communications, 164/10), and at the beginning of November had over
645,000 subscribers.





